records.addlTxt: Status conference on December 8, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
Status conference on December 8, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Barbara L Tate in court.  Prosecuting attorney Brendaliz Valdes in court for the State of Wisconsin. Clerk Dana A.  Minutes: DE is not eligible for SPD. DE given Advocate Counsel application in Court. Court holds colloquy with DE re: proceeding pro se or waiving time to allow SPD to appoint an attorney.  DE waives time for preliminary hearing. Court reschedules preliminary hearing to an attorney status hearing.  Bond continued with the addition DEFENDANT ALLOWED ADDITIONAL 24 HOURS TO HAVE A THIRD PARTY RETRIEVE PROPERTY. Status conference scheduled for December 8, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

PROPER ATTIRE REQUIRED.  NO SHORTS OR TANK TOPS ALLOWED IN COURTROOM. *Not to Possess or Consume Alcohol. *Not To Possess or Consume Controlled Substances w/o a Prescription. No contact including the residence, electronic or 3rd party with: Daniel T, Officer Patrick Newell unless in professional setting. The DE may make arrangements with a party or law enforcement to retrieve personal property and/or medication from the victim DT's residence within 24 hours of signing the bond in this case.  The DE may not be the party retrieving any property and/or medication.
